Tools and Technoligies Used:

1. Selenium: A framework for automating web browsers to simulate real-user interactions for UI testing.
2. Java version 11.0.16.1 : The programming language used to write the Selenium automation scripts and logic.
3. Maven 3.9.0: A build automation tool that manages project dependencies and automates the build and testing processes.
4. TestNG: A testing framework used for managing test execution, configurations.
5. Cucumber: A tool for writing behavior-driven tests in natural language using Gherkin syntax.
6. Allure Reporting: A reporting tool that generates visually appealing, detailed HTML test execution reports.


Steps For Run:
1. Clone the repo
2. Open the project on Intellij
3. Put your test data in src/test/java/Features/(.feature file)
4. Run your tests from the TestRunner class (src/test/java/Runner/TestRunner.java) or Use command (mvn clean test)
5. Run allure report using command (allure.bat serve .\allure-results\)

Note:
You can find a demo video in /video directory, in the code i added some Thread.sleep() to make the video more observable.

